{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EditorTranslationParserPlugin"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorTranslationParserPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" is invoked when a file is being parsed to extract strings that require translation. To define the parsing and string extraction logic, override the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorTranslationParserPlugin\/_parseFile(path:msgids:msgidsContextPlural:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method in script."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the extracted strings to argument ","type":"text"},{"code":"msgids","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"msgids_context_plural","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if context or plural is used."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When adding to "},{"code":"msgids_context_plural","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you must add the data using the format "},{"code":"[\"A\", \"B\", \"C\"]","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":" represents the extracted string, "},{"code":"B","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents the context, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"text":" represents the plural version of the extracted string. If you want to add only context but not plural, put ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for the plural slot. The idea is the same if you only want to add plural but not context. See the code below for concrete examples."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The extracted strings will be written into a POT file selected by user under “POT Generation” in “Localization” tab in “Project Settings” menu."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Below shows an example of a custom parser that extracts strings from a CSV file to write into a POT."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a translatable string associated with context or plural, add it to "},{"code":"msgids_context_plural","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you override parsing logic for standard script types (GDScript, C#, etc.), it would be better to load the ","type":"text"},{"code":"path","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" argument using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ResourceLoader\/load(path:typeHint:cacheMode:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". This is because built-in scripts are loaded as ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Resource"},{"text":" type, not ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/FileAccess"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorTranslationParserPlugin","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", register it using the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorPlugin\/addTranslationParserPlugin(parser:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method first."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"text